{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7392-fails-javac-compile-org.eclipse.angus-smtp-2.0.0-8a0a029a\n\nThe initial failing stage was `:compileTestJava`. `human-intervention-logs/org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T23-35-09-742321Z.log` shows `tests/src/org.eclipse.angus/smtp/2.0.0/src/test/java/org_eclipse_angus/smtp/SMTPTransportTest.java` still importing `com.sun.mail.smtp.SMTPTransport`, which no longer exists in Angus 2.0.0, and then failing on `assertThat(transport).isInstanceOf(SMTPTransport.class)`.\n\nThe most likely failing stage for this human-intervention run was the automation finalization/metrics handoff after the fix was found, not the library test itself. The generation log `human-intervention-logs/org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-20T23-35-50-985133Z.log` shows the import was updated to `org.eclipse.angus.mail.smtp.SMTPTransport`, and the later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T23-35-50-991461Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T23-36-38-065236Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-20T23-36-55-294611Z.log` all pass `compileTestJava`, `nativeTestCompile`, and `nativeTest`, with `SMTPTransportTest > fallsBackToLoginAfterCreatingSaslAuthenticator() SUCCESSFUL`. Despite that, `stats/org.eclipse.angus/smtp/2.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`.\n\n1. Inspect the preserved branch history and promote/cherry-pick commit `7bb089dfa1` if the import fix is acceptable.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.eclipse.angus:smtp:2.0.0` (or at least `compileTestJava` and `nativeTest`) to confirm the passing candidate outside the failed automation flow.\n3. If the rerun passes, investigate why the fix run was recorded as a failure with no artifacts despite successful Gradle reruns, and then clear or rerun the issue automation."}}
